### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### HEALTH
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 1. Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### AUTH — Register
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 2. Register — valid (copy accessToken from response into @accessToken above)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Ahmed Test",
  "email": "ahmed@example.com",
  "password": "Password1",
  "phone": "+92300000000",
  "newsletterOptIn": true
}

###

### 3. Register — duplicate email (should return 409)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Ahmed Again",
  "email": "ahmed@example.com",
  "password": "Password1"
}

###

### 4. Register — missing name (should return 422)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "noname@example.com",
  "password": "Password1"
}

###

### 5. Register — weak password, no uppercase (should return 422)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Weak Pass",
  "email": "weak@example.com",
  "password": "password1"
}

###

### 6. Register — weak password, no number (should return 422)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Weak Pass",
  "email": "weak2@example.com",
  "password": "Password"
}

###

### 7. Register — password too short (should return 422)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Short Pass",
  "email": "short@example.com",
  "password": "P1a"
}

###

### 8. Register — invalid email format (should return 422)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Bad Email",
  "email": "not-an-email",
  "password": "Password1"
}

###

### 9. Register admin user (manually update role in DB to "admin", then login below)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Admin User",
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "AdminPass1"
}


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### AUTH — Login
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 10. Login — valid (copy accessToken from response into @accessToken above)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "ahmed@example.com",
  "password": "Password1"
}

###

### 11. Login admin — valid (copy accessToken into @adminToken above)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "AdminPass1"
}

###

### 12. Login — wrong password (should return 401)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "ahmed@example.com",
  "password": "WrongPass1"
}

###

### 13. Login — email not registered (should return 401, same message as wrong password)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "ghost@example.com",
  "password": "Password1"
}

###

### 14. Login — missing password (should return 422)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "ahmed@example.com"
}

###

### 15. Login — empty body (should return 422)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{}


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### AUTH — Google OAuth
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 16. Google sign-in — valid (requires a real ID token from the frontend)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/google
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "idToken": "{{googleIdToken}}"
}

###

### 17. Google sign-in — missing idToken (should return 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/google
Content-Type: application/json

{}

###

### 18. Google sign-in — malformed token (should return 401)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/google
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "idToken": "this.is.not.a.real.google.token"
}


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### AUTH — Token refresh
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 19. Refresh — valid (refreshToken is sent automatically via httpOnly cookie;
###     if testing outside a browser you may need to copy the Set-Cookie header
###     value from a login response and paste it as a Cookie header below)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh

###

### 20. Refresh — no cookie present (should return 401)
### (send the request without any cookie — REST Client won't send cookies
###  automatically so this naturally tests the missing-token path)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
X-No-Cookie: true


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### AUTH — Me (protected)
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 21. Get current user — valid
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### 22. Get current user — no token (should return 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me

###

### 23. Get current user — malformed token (should return 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer this.is.not.valid

###

### 24. Get current user — expired token (should return 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJzdWIiOiJmYWtlLWlkIiwicm9sZSI6ImN1c3RvbWVyIiwiaWF0IjoxNjAwMDAwMDAwLCJleHAiOjE2MDAwMDAwMDF9.fake-signature


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### AUTH — Logout
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 25. Logout — valid (clears the refreshToken cookie)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout

###

### 26. Logout all devices — valid (requires auth)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout-all
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### 27. Logout all — no token (should return 401)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout-all


